vcjd is characterized by a relatively early age of onset (28 years) and prominent early psychiatric symptoms: anxiety, depression, agitation, delusions, and unpleasant sensory symptoms. neurological features are: unsteadiness, difficulty walking, and involuntary movements. memory loss progresses to severe cognitive impairment and, at the time of death, patients have become unable to move or speak. the median duration of illness is 14 months.
