sindbis virus (sinv), a single-stranded, positive sense, enveloped rna alphavirus, with 5 genotypes: sin i (european/african), sin ii and iii (asian/australian), sin iv (azerbaijan/china), and sin v (new zealand). the first sindbis virus isolated was cultured in 1952 from a mosquito near sindbis village in the nile delta (egypt). almost 10 years later the first human case was detected in uganda in 1961 and in europe in 1971.
