human t-lymphotropic virus 1 (htlv-1), a type c retrovirus with at least 6 subtypes. the virus was isolated for the first time in the usa in 1980, before hiv-1 (also a retrovirus) was discovered in 1983. genomically, simian t-lymphotropic virus (stlv) isolates cluster closely with htlv-1 in the same region, suggesting simian-to-human transmission at multiple occasions.
